The paper focuses on the practical experiences and value of using a software analytics platform to manage quality, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the development of the platform and its application to address software quality problems, which could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of semi-automated functionality and the integration of the platform into quality assurance activities could be relevant to the programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
